  "title": "A Bear Broke Into a Police Parking Lot. Nobody Was Cited.",
  "script": "A bear broke into WHERE? Castle Rock, Colorado's police department shared surveillance footage of a black bear — in the police parking lot. The bear scaled a chain-link fence, hopped onto a handrail, and shimmied its way over in what can only be described as a perfectly executed 180-degree pirouette at the top. Police called it a bear-icade breach. The bear conducted a brief pawspection of the area. Searched the lot. Found nothing. No picnic baskets, no unattended snacks, zero bear necessities. It eventually moved along. The whole thing was on camera, and the Castle Rock Police made every pun available. So: what exactly was this bear hoping a police parking lot had to offer?",
